A special thank you to @OhioState @OSUPrezDrake for inviting me to deliver the 2018 Autumn Commencement address & to @OSULibrary for displaying some of my collection from the OSU Archives @BuckeyeHistory. Good luck #OSUGrad Class of 2018! #TBDBITL pic.twitter.com/avi8fEHqWP
It was a humbling thrill of a lifetime to participate in Sunday’s OSU commencement ceremony. Congratulations to the #OSUGrad class of 2018!  #GoBucks #TBDBITL pic.twitter.com/dZpsyfnvSy

It is an honor beyond my wildest dreams that on Sunday, I will be delivering the commencement address at my beloved alma mater, The Ohio State University. 
Watch live @ 2pm at:  http://www.commencement.osu.edu/video.html  #GoBucks #TBDBITL

As your next Trustee, Larry will be dedicated to preserving our quality of life and ensuring that our first responders have the resources they need. On November 5th, vote Larry King for Genoa Township Trustee.
Larry has lived in Genoa for over 25 years, and he has devoted an incredible amount of time and effort for our safety forces and the building of a new police station.

It was an honor to represent Genoa Township in Congress for over 17 years. My wife and I chose to live in Genoa 15 years ago because it is a safe place to raise a family. That’s why I’m supporting Larry King for Township Trustee.
A big loss for The Dispatch and their central Ohio readers. Best of Luck!
